11
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:06,793
I came across a beast with two voices.

12
00:02:08,921 --> 00:02:10,964
I was thankful to have found a companion.

13
00:02:33,237 --> 00:02:34,029
Comon, sweetie.

14
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:38,116
Freak!

15
00:02:43,205 --> 00:02:44,790
Show's over, kid.

16
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:45,749
What's your name?

17
00:02:47,459 --> 00:02:50,170
Who...are...you?

18
00:03:02,391 --> 00:03:06,687
Soon I was taken to a new place with fences and sad faces.

19
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:35,257
<i>Note to self</i>

20
00:03:35,966 --> 00:03:37,885
<i>Be erect by half-past 10</i>

21
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:39,720
<i>Be strong, be proud...</i>

22
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:40,596
Lori!

23
00:03:46,018 --> 00:03:46,727
Lori!

24
00:03:49,271 --> 00:03:50,522
Are you getting up?

25
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:52,274
Declan!

26
00:03:57,404 --> 00:03:59,448
Let's all have breakfast together for a change!

27
00:03:59,448 --> 00:04:00,782
I'm making pancakes.

28
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:05,078
I think you've slept long enough.

29
00:04:08,123 --> 00:04:10,417
[PHONE RINGING]

30
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:12,586
Whew!

31
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:20,302
We, uh--we didn't get to finish what we started.

32
00:04:20,344 --> 00:04:21,762
You need to get out of here.

33
00:04:24,932 --> 00:04:25,849
Later, Trager.

34
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:32,314
Lou, you're not disturbing me.

35
00:04:32,773 --> 00:04:33,690
What's going on?

36
00:04:34,066 --> 00:04:36,109
[Lou] I got someone here I know you're going to want to meet.

37
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:39,655
The kid showed up here this morning and he's right up your alley.

38
00:04:40,030 --> 00:04:42,157
In other words, no one else wants to treat him.

39
00:04:42,241 --> 00:04:43,492
No, no, it's not like that.

40
00:04:43,784 --> 00:04:47,829
Nobody knows where he came from exactly, but he seems sharp and he's...

41
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:51,208
Look, you gotta see him for yourself.

42
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,835
I'll stop by at 10:00 tomorrow.

43
00:04:53,085 --> 00:04:55,003
Lo, um, this afternoon okay?

44
00:04:57,506 --> 00:04:58,757
I'm on my way.

45
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,555
Ah, it's alive!

46
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:05,764
Bite me.

47
00:05:06,181 --> 00:05:06,765
No, thanks.

48
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:07,850
That's Declan's job.

49
00:05:07,891 --> 00:05:09,268
Shut up, dweeb!

50
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:09,893
Declan?

51
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,436
What happened to Mike Suby?

52
00:05:12,062 --> 00:05:14,982
Old news. Declan's her new flavor of the month.

53
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,317
Or the week, in Miss Skanky's case.

54
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:18,235
Knock it off.

55
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:19,820
So, who's this Declan guy?

56
00:05:19,987 --> 00:05:20,863
He's just a friend.

57
00:05:20,863 --> 00:05:22,322
He's having a party this week.

58
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:23,490
Can I take the car?

59
00:05:23,907 --> 00:05:24,449
We'll see.

60
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:27,035
Sorry, guys. I have to go out for a bit.

61
00:05:27,202 --> 00:05:28,203
Go out?

62
00:05:28,245 --> 00:05:29,413
Lou Daniels just called.

63
00:05:29,496 --> 00:05:30,581
Nicole, it's Sunday.

64
00:05:30,664 --> 00:05:33,333
I know, but it's urgent and it sounds like a really special case.

65
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:34,668
They always do.

66
00:05:35,294 --> 00:05:37,087
Save some pancakes for me, okay?

67
00:05:53,437 --> 00:05:54,813
Yeah, let's roll, man.

68
00:05:57,191 --> 00:06:02,279
For some reason, the more people I saw, the more alone I felt.

69
00:06:06,074 --> 00:06:08,202
Yo, let's get some juice down here.

70
00:06:11,288 --> 00:06:13,332
'Sup? Everyone taking stupid pills around here?

71
00:06:13,248 --> 00:06:14,333
Juice me!

72
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:37,731
Most of our time is spent trying to lessen the pains of life.

73
00:06:39,066 --> 00:06:41,360
I was about to learn how to quash hunger.

74
00:07:06,635 --> 00:07:07,970
See something you like, punk?

75
00:07:08,387 --> 00:07:10,264
You gonna see my fist if you don't quit eyeballing me.

76
00:07:11,723 --> 00:07:13,141
Kick his ass, man.

77
00:07:19,648 --> 00:07:21,149
Be cool, Skeeter.

78
00:07:21,358 --> 00:07:23,110
He can't understand a word you say.

79
00:07:23,527 --> 00:07:24,862
He ain't dissin' you, man.

80
00:07:26,321 --> 00:07:27,281
A'ight.

81
00:07:28,198 --> 00:07:29,324
He keeps staring at me,

82
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:32,369
I'm gonna have to kick his sorry ass.

83
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:39,084
I had no reason to fear this person,
but he reminded me of the snake in the woods, just before it struck.

84
00:08:06,862 --> 00:08:11,533
I was glad to see a familiar face,
but a pressure below my waist was bothering me.

85
00:08:19,124 --> 00:08:20,501
Come on, show me what you got.

86
00:08:22,628 --> 00:08:23,170
Come on, put your hands up!

87
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:23,879
Put 'em up!

88
00:08:25,547 --> 00:08:26,965
You ain't tough, new kid.

89
00:08:27,007 --> 00:08:27,799
Come on, put em' up!

90
00:08:28,717 --> 00:08:29,092
Come on!

91
00:08:32,471 --> 00:08:33,680
[Boy] Knock him out, Skeeter!

92
00:08:40,771 --> 00:08:45,317
I wanted to learn his game,
but the pain in my belly was getting more intense.

93
00:08:51,114 --> 00:08:51,615
Hey!

94
00:08:55,827 --> 00:09:04,211
I barely noticed the discomfort on my face because inside me,
something had flipped and I began to feel wonderful.

95
00:09:04,711 --> 00:09:05,921
[Lou] Great job, guys!

96
00:09:06,338 --> 00:09:07,923
No rec privileges for a week.

97
00:09:08,423 --> 00:09:09,466
Now get out of here!

98
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:11,134
Now!

99
00:09:12,553 --> 00:09:14,054
Everybody out!

100
00:09:27,109 --> 00:09:28,068
Hey,  Nicole.

101
00:09:28,735 --> 00:09:30,112
Thanks for coming by to see him.

102
00:09:30,112 --> 00:09:31,446
Does "him" have a name?

103
00:09:31,864 --> 00:09:34,658
The paperwork says "John Doe» for the time being.

104
00:09:34,658 --> 00:09:35,868
John Doe.

105
00:09:36,118 --> 00:09:38,370
What's a handsome boy like that doing with a dead man's name?

106
00:09:39,204 --> 00:09:41,748
You know he kind of reminds me of my brother Kyle.

107
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:45,210
He got all the looks in the family.

108
00:09:46,003 --> 00:09:47,087
That's perfect.

109
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:48,338
Kyle.

110
00:09:52,176 --> 00:09:53,093
Y eah.

111
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:56,930
Can't speak a word, but damned if he doesn't know what you're saying.

112
00:09:59,266 --> 00:10:00,976
I'll be outside if you need me.

113
00:10:01,018 --> 00:10:01,476
Okay.

114
00:10:26,251 --> 00:10:29,880
I wanted to show her where I'd come from and what I had seen.

115
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:51,151
So let me understand.

116
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:55,989
The boy has no family that you know of, he doesn't communicate, and he was found just wandering alone in the city?

117
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:57,991
That's all his "Booked Into Shelter" folder said.

118
00:10:57,991 --> 00:11:00,369
No Amber Alerts, no missing persons report, nothing.

119
00:11:00,786 --> 00:11:03,497
But there is one more things you should see.

120
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,126
No belly button.

121
00:11:13,298 --> 00:11:14,675
They're never gonna go for this.

122
00:11:14,591 --> 00:11:15,676
It's just for a few days.

123
00:11:15,676 --> 00:11:17,344
-Finally. I'm starving!

124
00:11:17,261 --> 00:11:18,387
-Did you get lo mein?

125
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:19,680
Hold on a minute.

126
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:20,848
Your mom's got something to talk to you about.

127
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:26,395
I have a new patient, and the place where he's staying isn't safe, so I'm bringing him here for a little while.

128
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:28,814
You mean some mental patient's going to live in our house?

129
00:11:28,939 --> 00:11:30,357
He's not a mental patient.

130
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:32,609
He's a very sweet, very special boy.

131
00:11:32,484 --> 00:11:34,027
I know what "very special" means.

132
00:11:33,861 --> 00:11:35,320
He'll probably drool all over the house.

133
00:11:35,279 --> 00:11:39,449
I have to say, I have thought--I'd hoped
that you would both show a little compassion.

134
00:11:39,241 --> 00:11:40,534
You don't even know this kid.

135
00:11:40,325 --> 00:11:41,618
I don't want him touching my things.

136
00:11:41,451 --> 00:11:42,786
All right, that's enough.

137
00:11:42,619 --> 00:11:45,164
If your mom says he's coming, he's coming and that's final.

138
00:11:56,717 --> 00:12:00,429
<i>So you're born on the cusp</i>

139
00:12:00,429 --> 00:12:03,432
<i>Or it's a run of bad luck</i>

140
00:12:04,183 --> 00:12:06,685
<i>But it's bigger than us...</i>

141
00:12:07,144 --> 00:12:08,103
This is it.

142
00:12:08,979 --> 00:12:09,396
Home.

143
00:12:12,441 --> 00:12:17,070
Where you're gonna be staying for a few days, at least until I can...

144
00:12:26,038 --> 00:12:29,750
[Kyle] My first thought was that flat,
tiny people must be living in the walls.

145
00:12:32,211 --> 00:12:33,545
But then I understood.

146
00:12:34,213 --> 00:12:38,634
Humans grow smaller as they develop and pretty soon,
I'd be shrinking, myself.

147
00:12:45,682 --> 00:12:48,852
Maybe one day this woman would hold me, too.

148
00:12:58,946 --> 00:13:03,283
The images made my mind explode with complex mathematical formulae.

149
00:13:04,576 --> 00:13:06,286
Would you like to play a game, Kyle?

150
00:13:06,495 --> 00:13:07,162
Here.

151
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:10,624
Lots of kids have tons of fun with this one.

152
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:14,837
This is called a mouse.

153
00:13:15,128 --> 00:13:17,089
When you move it, this arrow--

154
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:23,053
Hello there.

155
00:13:23,053 --> 00:13:24,388
-[phone ringing]
-I am a bird.

156
00:13:24,721 --> 00:13:26,515
I fly high into the sky.

157
00:13:26,515 --> 00:13:28,600
Touch the sky and watch me fly.

158
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,269
-Hello?
-How'd it go? Did you bring him home?

159
00:13:30,269 --> 00:13:32,187
Oh, he's just great. He's on the computer right now.

160
00:13:32,312 --> 00:13:34,398
Do you need me there? Could be a lot to handle.

161
00:13:34,398 --> 00:13:36,066
Trust me, honey, I'll be fine.

162
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,818
Look at the house.

163
00:13:37,818 --> 00:13:40,320
Getting a little old for Barney, aren't we, Josh?

164
00:13:43,574 --> 00:13:47,119
[Kyle] When I saw her, I realized something was horribly wrong.

165
00:13:47,661 --> 00:13:51,415
Humans grow larger over time, not smaller.

166
00:13:51,748 --> 00:13:54,877
It bothered me. Wasn't I ever small?

167
00:13:55,502 --> 00:13:57,004
Why didn't you tell me he was in the house?

168
00:13:57,004 --> 00:13:58,130
I think he saw my boobs!

169
00:13:58,672 --> 00:14:00,674
What did she-- Did he just--

170
00:14:00,674 --> 00:14:02,384
Stephen, I promise, we're fine.

171
00:14:02,176 --> 00:14:04,011
I've got another call. I've gotta go.

172
00:14:08,515 --> 00:14:16,565
Our top story in Trebourne County:
a teenage girl washed up on shore this morning,
having no memory whatsoever of how she got there.

173
00:14:16,481 --> 00:14:19,026
[Computer] Fractions, fractions, all done!

174
00:14:19,318 --> 00:14:20,360
Yum yum!

175
00:14:20,485 --> 00:14:21,695
How much blood?

176
00:14:22,029 --> 00:14:23,363
Okay, I'm on my way.

177
00:14:24,031 --> 00:14:26,617
Listen, theres an emergency at work.

178
00:14:26,617 --> 00:14:27,492
I need you to watch Kyle.

179
00:14:28,118 --> 00:14:29,536
-Sure, Mom.
-I'm serious!

180
00:14:29,536 --> 00:14:30,454
Watch him.

181
00:14:31,288 --> 00:14:32,122
I'll be right back.

182
00:14:36,752 --> 00:14:37,794
H ello?

183
00:14:38,754 --> 00:14:39,755
Oh, hi, Hillary.

184
00:14:40,214 --> 00:14:44,092
No, Declan still hasn't called, and if he's with Jessica, he's probably got the clap by now.

185
00:14:45,469 --> 00:14:48,764
You know me. I felt weird when Mike Suby put his hand down my pants.

186
00:14:50,557 --> 00:14:53,018
Because all I could think about were these warts on his hand.

187
00:14:54,186 --> 00:14:55,354
That could be him!

188
00:14:55,771 --> 00:14:57,147
If I don't click over, you'll know why.

189
00:14:59,525 --> 00:15:00,901
Hello?

190
00:15:01,652 --> 00:15:02,903
Oh, hi, Declan.

191
00:15:03,612 --> 00:15:05,197
No, I wasn't talking to anyone. What's up?

192
00:15:06,615 --> 00:15:09,785
[laughter] I know.

193
00:15:18,043 --> 00:15:20,128
[Kyle] It was the most beautiful sound in the world.

194
00:15:35,185 --> 00:15:38,856
It was part mathematics and part... euphoria.

195
00:15:49,741 --> 00:15:56,456
I felt certain that whatever this was, was a gift to the world, meant to fill all that heard it with a flood of emotion.

196
00:15:59,168 --> 00:16:00,878
[Woman] Amanda, I'm home!

197
00:16:06,049 --> 00:16:09,636
It then struck me that not everyone could appreciate this miracle.

198
00:16:10,345 --> 00:16:13,265
The sound increased my sorrow for those who could not hear it.

199
00:16:32,284 --> 00:16:34,036
There was a pounding in my chest.

200
00:16:34,411 --> 00:16:39,708
My face felt like it was burning, and more than anything,
I wanted to disappear.

201
00:17:09,238 --> 00:17:11,615
Aah! Aah!

202
00:17:15,869 --> 00:17:17,871
Run, Mom! There's a psycho in the shower!

203
00:17:25,629 --> 00:17:26,880
It's okay, Josh.

204
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:27,965
It's okay.

205
00:17:28,173 --> 00:17:31,134
This is Kyle, the special boy I was telling you about.

206
00:17:31,385 --> 00:17:34,346
If he's supposed to be so special, why'd you stick him in the bathtub?

207
00:17:35,514 --> 00:17:37,307
Nice to meet you... perv.

208
00:17:38,892 --> 00:17:42,271
The reason I am letting that slide is because I have a favor to ask of you.

209
00:17:42,271 --> 00:17:46,066
I would like Kyle to bunk down in your room for a couple nights.

210
00:17:46,066 --> 00:17:47,067
Are you kidding?

211
00:17:47,067 --> 00:17:49,152
This guy's got "bed wetter" written all over him.

212
00:17:49,152 --> 00:17:50,529
Well, I'm only asking.

213
00:17:54,116 --> 00:17:55,284
Fine.

214
00:17:55,325 --> 00:17:57,452
But you better bustle out the rubber sheets.

215
00:17:57,536 --> 00:18:00,289
Have you seen Lori? She was supposed to be watching him.

216
00:18:00,831 --> 00:18:02,875
Some teacher called with test results...

217
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:05,377
Mrs....Planny Parenthood.

218
00:18:05,669 --> 00:18:10,174
I  was beginning to sense that my very presence was turning these people against each other.

219
00:18:14,178 --> 00:18:15,888
You and I are gonna have a talk.

220
00:18:16,305 --> 00:18:18,599
Oh, no. Did something happen to Kyle?

221
00:18:18,557 --> 00:18:21,226
Oh, you mean besides him going outside by himself?

222
00:18:23,478 --> 00:18:25,647
You can forget about Declan's party.

223
00:18:36,575 --> 00:18:40,579
<i>Look out your front door, there's a ship coming in...</i>

224
00:18:43,081 --> 00:18:44,166
Hi, honey.

225
00:18:44,708 --> 00:18:47,252
Hey, something wrong with Lori? She seems upset about something.

226
00:18:47,252 --> 00:18:50,297
She's just having a difficult time understanding what responsibility means.

227
00:18:50,380 --> 00:18:50,797
Oh.

228
00:18:51,131 --> 00:18:52,424
Is this the, uh...?

229
00:18:53,091 --> 00:18:55,260
Kyle, this is my husband Stephen.

230
00:18:55,344 --> 00:18:56,720
Honey, this is Kyle.

231
00:18:57,387 --> 00:18:58,889
Hello, Kyle.

232
00:19:01,892 --> 00:19:05,395
[slowly] I'm happy to make your acquaintance.

233
00:19:06,897 --> 00:19:08,899
Can he understand a single thing I'm saying?

234
00:19:08,774 --> 00:19:09,775
I don't think so.

235
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:11,944
Well, at least he doesn't look dangerous.

236
00:19:13,111 --> 00:19:14,655
Oh! Watch it, watch it!

237
00:19:14,988 --> 00:19:16,990
It's hot! Hot! Ouch!

238
00:19:17,032 --> 00:19:18,242
Ow, ow, ow!

239
00:19:18,283 --> 00:19:20,869
This being was clearly a superior communicator.

240
00:19:21,745 --> 00:19:26,917
I somehow understood everything it said and wondered
why others chose to speak so ineffectively.

241
00:19:33,882 --> 00:19:38,220
You know, this neighborhood isn't zoned for halfway houses

242
00:19:38,554 --> 00:19:39,721
Oh, good evening, by the way.

243
00:19:39,721 --> 00:19:40,639
Excuse me?

244
00:19:41,014 --> 00:19:43,475
One of your challenged cases broke into my--

245
00:19:43,475 --> 00:19:44,518
He didn't break in, Mom.

246
00:19:45,102 --> 00:19:50,190
Broke into my house this afternoon and snuck up on Amanda while she was alone.

247
00:19:50,816 --> 00:19:53,235
Who knows what could've happened if I hadn't come home when I did.

248
00:19:53,277 --> 00:19:55,487
I'm so sorry, Carol.

249
00:19:55,529 --> 00:19:58,323
Lori was responsible for watching Kyle this afternoon--

250
00:19:58,407 --> 00:20:01,493
Nicole, I would hate to make this into a police matter...

251
00:20:06,456 --> 00:20:07,916
Come along, Amanda.

252
00:20:10,627 --> 00:20:11,712
I'll see ya later!

253
00:20:18,051 --> 00:20:19,303
It's not fair, Dad.

254
00:20:19,386 --> 00:20:20,179
I was in the next room.

255
00:20:20,179 --> 00:20:22,514
It's not like I left him alone with Michael Jackson.

256
00:20:23,432 --> 00:20:26,226
There are over 800,000 words in the English language.

